decks.notes: The deck is focused on assembling and resolving the combo of Doomsday with Thassa's Oracle to win the game by eliminating the opponent's entire library. The deck includes powerful cards like Black Lotus, Force of Will, and Necropotence to support the combo and protect it from disruption. It also includes card selection and card draw spells like Ponder, Brainstorm, and Dig Through Time to find the combo pieces quickly. Overall, the deck aims to quickly assemble the combo and win the game in a few turns.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan with hatebears like Anointed Peacekeeper, Archon of Emeria, and Thalia, Guardian of Thraben, while also applying pressure with aggressive creatures like Seasoned Dungeoneer and White Plume Adventurer. By utilizing cards like Cavern of Souls and Chancellor of the Annex, it aims to protect its creatures from countermagic and disrupt the opponent's spells. The deck also includes powerful artifacts like Black Lotus and Moxen for fast mana acceleration, along with disruptive spells like Trinisphere and Swords to Plowshares for added control.

The main concept of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive artifact creatures and disrupt their game plan with disruptive artifacts like Trinisphere, Null Rod, and Chalice of the Void. The deck aims to control the game by utilizing Mishra's Workshop and other mana acceleration artifacts to play threats like Golos, Tireless Pilgrim and Stonecoil Serpent quickly. It also has cards like Crucible of Worlds and Ghost Quarter to disrupt the opponent's mana base. The deck is focused on establishing early board presence and controlling the game with disruptive artifacts in order to win quickly.

The deck utilizes the Oath of Druids combo to cheat out powerful creatures like Atraxa, Grand Unifier and Narset, Parter of Veils early in the game. It also includes a variety of counterspells like Force of Will and Force of Negation to control the opponent's plays. The deck has a solid card draw engine with Ancestral Recall, Dig Through Time, and Preordain. Show and Tell is included as an alternate way to get big threats onto the battlefield. Overall, the deck aims to control the game and overwhelm the opponent with powerful creatures.

The deck focuses on generating mana quickly with powerful artifacts like Mana Vault, Mana Crypt, and the Moxen, while also using card draw and manipulation spells like Sensei's Divining Top and Brainstorm. The key strategy is to set up a big turn where you can play Paradoxical Outcome to bounce your artifacts back to hand and draw a huge number of cards, generating even more mana and resources to win the game in one explosive turn. The deck is designed to be efficient and consistent in executing this combo strategy.
